    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.48/9–144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Personal Representative at Vatican City</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Taylor</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President and the
                            Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">strictly confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vatican City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-01">September 1,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This message is urgent and strictly confidential for the President and the
                    Secretary.</p>
                <p>It is extremely important before your reported conference with the Prime Minister
                    that you have a frank talk with General O’Dwyer regarding Italy, its relief
                    needs, and plans to meet the situation. To accomplish this will you request
                    Secretary Hull or Leo Crowley to telegraph O’Dwyer personally to report to
                    Washington for consultation without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
